postcontent:
The Romanian SAR-1. The SAR series of rifles is well known through the gun community as being one of the only AK-47 rifles imported into the United States on an original military specification receiver. They are known for excellent quality and extreme reliability (unlike the current Romanian WASR rifles) Almost all other AK 47 rifles in the country were either built here using other countries parts or imported as low capacity rifles and then drilled out for full magazines here in the States. Not so with the SAR rifles, they were built as they are in the country that makes them for their military. The SAR-1 is a fantastic weapon, combining the durability and ruggedness of the AK-47 with the lightweight ammo and accuracy of the American 7.62x39 round. Not only do you have a weapon that just won't stop, but you have an ammo supply of one of America's favorite calibers to keep the weapon fed in the event of foreign ammo shortages.

title: For Sale:  Desert Eagle NIB
postcontent:
The Desert Eagle uses a gas-operated mechanism normally found in rifles, as opposed to the short recoil or blow-back designs most commonly seen in semi-automatic pistols. When a round is fired, gases are ported out through a small hole in the barrel near the breech. These travel forward through a small tube under the barrel, to a cylinder near the front of the barrel. The separate bolt carrier/slide has a small piston on the front that fits into this cylinder; when the gases reach the cylinder they push the piston rearward. The bolt carrier rides rearward on two rails on either side of the barrel, operating the mechanism. Its rotating bolt strongly resembles that of the M16 series of rifles, while the fixed gas cylinder/moving piston resemble those of the Ruger Mini-14 carbine (the original patent used a captive piston similar to the M14 rifle).The advantage of the gas operation is that it allows the use of far more powerful cartridges than traditional semi-automatic pistol designs. Thus it allows the Desert Eagle to compete in an area that had previously been dominated by magnum revolvers. Downsides of the gas-operated mechanism are the large size of the Desert Eagle, and the fact that it discourages the use of unjacketed lead bullets, as lead particles sheared off during firing could clog the gas release tap, preventing proper function. Switching a Desert Eagle to another chambering requires only that the correct barrel, bolt assembly, and magazine be installed. Thus, a conversion to fire the other cartridges can be quickly accomplished. The rim diameter of the .50 AE (Action Express) is the same as the .44 Remington Magnum cartridge, consequently only a barrel and magazine change is required to convert a .44 Desert Eagle to the larger, more powerful .50 AE round.The most popular barrel length is 6 in (152 mm), although a 10 in (254 mm) barrel is available. The Mark XIX barrels are machined with integral scope mounting bases, simplifying the process of adding a pistol scope.

The Desert Eagle is fed with a detachable magazine. Magazine capacity is 9 rounds in .357 Magnum, 8 rounds in .44 Magnum, and 7 rounds in .50 Action Express. The Desert Eagle's barrel features polygonal rifling. The pistol is primarily used for hunting, target shooting, and silhouette shooting

DISINTEGRATOR®
 No one equips you for perfect practice like Remington, which is why we’re the top choice for government agencies everywhere – in the field and on the range. Disintegrator lead free frangible ammunition is a technological breakthrough in bullet construction that offers totally lead free, no-ricochet performance, with point of impact and felt recoil equivalent to standard lead core pistol ammunition. In accuracy performance, it is as good or better than the best duty ammo. Disintegrator frangible bullets feature a high strength compaction formed core, completely sealed in a jacket of electroplated copper. The metal powder core construction creates a bullet that easily withstands the forces and pressures of firing, while providing instant and complete frangibility against hard surfaces. The copper plating on Disintegrator bullets provide a smooth ductile jacket that enhances feed and function in all autoloading pistols, minimizes bore fouling, and virtually eliminates barrel erosion. Only 0.005” thick, it is enough for rifling engraving, but too thin to ricochet. Disintegrator bullets are made of compressed metal particles shaped into standard profile 9mm, .40 S&W, and .45 ACP specifications. Disintegrator core is completely protected with hard copper plate. title: For Sale:  Brand New CAR 15 Pre-Ban !!! 223/5.56 AR15
postcontent:
This is the real deal original CAR-15!!!  This is one of the nicest and best quality ARs you can buy. And to get a new, unfired one is very rare. You get to break it in properly and have a weapon you know you can count on because nobody else has ever used it! And it's new in the box so no matter what assault weapons ban comes, this is a true pre-ban original!!

This is the original AR platform - the CAR 15
Here is the full info:

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CAR-15

Here is a link to one that sold recently with the long barrel which is much more common:

http://www.gunsamerica.com/921536447/Olympic_CAR_15_pre_ban_Pristine_condition.htm

This is a brand new, never fired classic. When these were being made in the late 80's they were by far one of the best quality AR on the market. They are not made to this quality nowadays. Ive decided there are some other toys I want more than this one so Im selling it. Its been stored now for over 20 years! 
The serial number is V followed by 4 digits. You can confirm the manufacture date on Oly Arms website "What does my serial number mean" webpage. 

This has the impossible to find 11.5 barrel with 5.5 permanently attached supressor making it meet the 16" barrel length requirement. This is an extremely rare rifle!

This has the highly desired SS 1 in 7" barrel like our soldiers use and chromed bore and chamber for optimum performance and durability. It still all stock with the original box and accessories. 



Im taking cash and trade offers. 
From my research these seem to start at about 2K for a pre-ban 80's model, never fired. And it's almost impossible to find one with the 11.5" barrel. I'm not looking to get every last dollar on this but I'd take the lower end of what these appear to be bringing. 

I also have about AR mags and I can include as many as you want for the right price. See my other listings. 

Im located basically on the DE/PA/MD border. I prefer FTF sale but can do shipping to FFL.

I have sold several rifles from me personal colection and can email you the previous listings and contact info for the buyers who I have shipped to. 
Beware of the really low prices - if its too good to be true, it probably is.

title: For Sale:  Swiss K31 rifle
postcontent:
Arguably the most accurate of the WW2 battle rifles featuring the lightning fast, straight pull,  bolt action chambered in 7.5 X 55 mm.  The 23 1/2 in. barrel can easily be made to free float yielding accuracy approaching 1 MOA with surplus, inexpensive, high quality Swiss ammo.  I reload my own ammo using a .308 dia. bullet but ammo is available from Hornady, Privi and other mfgrs.  Ballistically, this cartridge has 15 to 20% more muzzle energy than a standard .308 cartridge which is more than adequate for any North American game (Grizzley bear?).

If you are a collecter of military firearms this "excellent grade" firearm would be a great  addition to your collection...these rifles  have seen a 50% + increase in value in the last 5 years.

It has a walnut stock, 90% + bluing, 3 1/2 lb. trigger, and a bright shiny bore.  I am asking $475, but will consider offers.

I live in Grand Marais, MN but can arrange a meeting in Duluth or perhaps locations further south toward the Twin cities.
